## 2. Typography & Fonts

### Adding Google Fonts

Update `src/app/layout.tsx` to import client's fonts:

```tsx
// Location: src/app/layout.tsx

import { Inter, Roboto, Open_Sans } from "next/font/google";

// Configure primary font
const primaryFont = Inter({
  variable: "--font-primary",
  subsets: ["latin"],
  weight: ["300", "400", "500", "600", "700"],
  display: "swap",
});

// Configure secondary font (if needed)
const secondaryFont = Roboto({
  variable: "--font-secondary",
  subsets: ["latin"],
  weight: ["400", "500", "700"],
  display: "swap",
});

// Apply in body tag
<body className={`${primaryFont.variable} ${secondaryFont.variable}`}>
  <StyledComponentsRegistry>{children}</StyledComponentsRegistry>
</body>;
```

### Using Custom/Licensed Fonts

For custom fonts (not available on Google Fonts):

1. **Add font files to `/public/fonts/`**:

   ```
   /public/fonts/
     CustomFont-Regular.woff2
     CustomFont-Bold.woff2
   ```

2. **Define @font-face in `src/styles/main.scss`**:

   ```scss
   @font-face {
     font-family: "Custom Font";
     src: url("/fonts/CustomFont-Regular.woff2") format("woff2");
     font-weight: 400;
     font-style: normal;
     font-display: swap;
   }

   @font-face {
     font-family: "Custom Font";
     src: url("/fonts/CustomFont-Bold.woff2") format("woff2");
     font-weight: 700;
     font-style: normal;
     font-display: swap;
   }
   ```

3. **Update CSS variables**:
   ```scss
   :root {
     --font-primary: "Custom Font", system-ui, sans-serif;
   }
   ```

### Font Guidelines

- **Always include fallback fonts**: `'Primary Font', system-ui, sans-serif`
- **Use `font-display: swap`**: Prevents invisible text during font load
- **Subset fonts**: Include only needed character sets (usually "latin")
- **Optimize weights**: Only include font weights you'll actually use
- **Test loading**: Check font loading on slow connections

