## 3. Metadata & SEO

### Update Site Metadata

Edit `src/app/layout.tsx` to reflect client information:

```tsx
// Location: src/app/layout.tsx

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  metadataBase: new URL("https://client-domain.com"), // ← Update URL
  title: {
    default: "Client Company Name", // ← Update
    template: "Client Company Name | %s", // ← Update
  },
  description: "Client's business description and value proposition.", // ← Update
  keywords: ["client industry", "services", "location"], // ← Update
  authors: [{ name: "Client Company Name" }], // ← Update
  creator: "Your Agency Name",
  publisher: "Client Company Name",
  robots: {
    index: true, // Set false for staging sites
    follow: true,
    googleBot: {
      index: true,
      follow: true,
    },
  },
  openGraph: {
    type: "website",
    locale: "en_US",
    url: "https://client-domain.com", // ← Update
    siteName: "Client Company Name", // ← Update
    title: "Client Company Name - Tagline", // ← Update
    description: "Client's business description.", // ← Update
    images: [
      {
        url: "/og-image.png", // Must be 1200x630px
        width: 1200,
        height: 630,
        alt: "Client Company Name", // ← Update
        type: "image/png",
      },
    ],
  },
  alternates: {
    canonical: "https://client-domain.com", // ← Update
  },
  icons: {
    icon: [{ url: "/favicon.ico", type: "image/x-icon" }],
    shortcut: "/favicon.ico",
  },
};
```

### Metadata Checklist

- [ ] Update `metadataBase` with production URL
- [ ] Set descriptive page title
- [ ] Write compelling description (150-160 characters)
- [ ] Add relevant keywords
- [ ] Update OpenGraph title and description
- [ ] Set correct canonical URL
- [ ] Verify robots settings (noindex for staging!)

