## 5. Environment Variables

### Create .env.local

Copy `.env.example` to `.env.local` and fill in client-specific values:

```bash
# Application
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://client-domain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=Client Company Name

# Analytics (if applicable)
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# API Keys (add as needed)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api.client-domain.com
API_SECRET_KEY=secret_value_here

# Third-party Services
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.xxxxx
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_xxxxx
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_xxxxx
```

### Environment Variable Guidelines

- **Public variables**: Prefix with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` (exposed to browser)
- **Secret variables**: No prefix (server-only)
- **Never commit**: Keep `.env.local` out of git
- **Document in .env.example**: Add placeholders for all required vars
- **Production**: Set variables in hosting platform (Vercel, etc.)

